President Obama addressed the shooting in San Bernardino, expressing condolences to the families of the victims and thanking law enforcement for their response. He stated that it is still unclear why the shooting occurred and the motivations behind it. The FBI is leading the investigation, considering the possibility that it may be terrorist-related or workplace-related. The President emphasized the need for everyone to play a part in preventing such incidents and mentioned the importance of implementing measures to make it harder for individuals to access weapons. He mentioned that there will be a press conference led by the Attorney General later in the day and reassured that the investigation will continue until all the facts are uncovered. The President concluded by offering his deepest condolences to those affected by the tragedy.